/*** How to run the program ***
*******************************

1. Type "make" from the a1 directory. 

2. The Makefile will send the executable to the bin folder.

3. Navigate to bin folder and type ./run 

4. When you either win or tie, type any key to start a new game. 

5. Press 'q' at any time to exit the game.*/

/*** About the program ***
**************************

1. The program will prevent the user from placing a marker over top of another game piece.
2. The program will determine if their was a tie.
3. The program will prevent the user from moving out of bounds. */
 

/*** Known errors ***
*********************

After you win or tie, for every SECOND game the grid will not appear. This does not affect gameplay.
on your next try the grid will re-appear */